6
00:01:44,221 --> 00:01:45,742
Kiss 'em good-bye for me, Maury.

7
00:01:45,822 --> 00:01:48,182
I'll miss 'em...
like hell I will.

8
00:01:48,223 --> 00:01:49,261
Dreamin' again.

9
00:01:49,262 --> 00:01:51,544
Not anymore, Lil.
I'm awake now,

10
00:01:51,584 --> 00:01:54,585
awake for the first time in years.

11
00:01:54,664 --> 00:01:56,025
Uncle Dave said it...

12
00:01:56,105 --> 00:01:57,465
"Daylight is a dream

13
00:01:57,505 --> 00:01:59,985
if you live with your eyes closed."

14
00:02:00,066 --> 00:02:02,906
Well, my eyes are open now.
I see the choir.

15
00:02:02,986 --> 00:02:04,947
I know they're dressed in rags,

16
00:02:05,027 --> 00:02:07,107
but we're part of that choir.

17
00:02:07,188 --> 00:02:08,468
Yeah, both of us,

18
00:02:08,548 --> 00:02:10,708
and you, Maury, and Uncle Dave.

19
00:02:10,789 --> 00:02:12,149
Sun's comin' up, kid.

20
00:02:12,189 --> 00:02:13,869
They'll be hawkin' the fish

21
00:02:13,950 --> 00:02:15,310
down on Fulton Street.

22
00:02:15,390 --> 00:02:16,750
Let 'em hawk.

23
00:02:16,831 --> 00:02:18,831
Let 'em sing their hearts out.

24
00:02:18,910 --> 00:02:20,111
That's it, kid.

25
00:02:20,191 --> 00:02:22,512
Take that ruined choir.
Make it sing.

26
00:02:22,592 --> 00:02:23,872
So long, Maury.

27
00:02:23,952 --> 00:02:25,352
So long.

28
00:02:27,553 --> 00:02:29,233
We'll hear from that kid,

29
00:02:29,314 --> 00:02:31,954
and I don't mean a postcard.

30
